cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on the task of affordance detection for robotic grasping, which is a core problem in robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The proposed approach uses RGB-D images to learn grasping features, which is a common task in computer vision. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep learning approach to learn grasping features from RGB-D images, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based approach to enable robots to interact with the environment by predicting grasp configurations. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper uses a subset of ShapeNetCore dataset, which is a 3D object dataset commonly used in computer graphics.
